Hello all!

I really am ashamed while typing this, because I just thought I 
hadn't notified you that the vote for fr.comp.lang.caml had started!!
:(
3 weeks that it's on now and the problem is there isn't a lot of time 
left for you to vote, as it will be over on June 25, which means that 
you'll have to vote this week-end, or your post will *not* be taken 
into account.
So if you want such a news-group to be created (either you plan to 
take part or you just want to support it), my advise is to be quick, 
since this is your last chance to add a drop of functional mind in 
news:fr.comp.lang.*  which hardly has any at present...

All you have to do is follow the intructions in message 
<3b2dae2b.919760856@ulva.exo.neottia.net>, which was posted in 
fr.usenet.forums.annonces 

If you do not know what to do but still want to vote, you can tell me 
by mail  ("Micky" <micky.esra@freesbee.fr>), and I'll do it for you. In this
case, be sure you enter a 
valid email address in the 'From' field.

I sincerely apologize for being so stupid and late, but this is the 
way I am, so I just hope that you people who wanted to vote will 
manage it before it's too late...

Thank you!

